    "[252] 2023 Legal Setting \"AI hallucination\" occurs when LLMs generate misleading text and information. 234 Xin et al.",
    "[253] 2023 Dialogue \"AI hallucination\" refers to the occurrence where pretrained text generation models occasionally generate text that is nonsensical or unfaithful to the provided source input. 235 Murgia et al.",
    "[254] 2023 ChatGPT \"AI hallucination\" occurs when generative LLMs generate unintended text, leading to degraded system performance and unmet user expectations in real-world scenarios. 236 Kunze et al.",
    "[255] 2023 Large Language Model \"AI hallucination\" refers to the phenomenon where the GPT model appears to be designed to provide incorrect answers rather than admit this to its users.",
    "237 Cascella [256] 2023 Academia \"AI hallucination\" refers to ChatGPT generating answers that sound credible but may be incorrect or nonsensical."
